The reason for magicians not getting root doesnt have anything to do with offence. Its because magicians get good pets as defence instead. Wizards gets root and snare, but no pets. Necromancers get defensivly weaker pets, but defensive spells as well. Wizards and magicians both have their defense tied up in one area.<br>
=====================<br>
<br>
Well, comparing to wizards, our pets are somewhat equal, offensively, to their better nukes. Considering that, now consider that root is 100 times better and more versatile than pets defensively. This leaves us a bit behind.<br>
<br>
And how do I presume mage is balanced to wiz offensively? Well, wizard out damages us in short period of time. In a long period of time, we typically out damage them. Equal, but different.<br>
<br>
And how do I presume pet is not root defensively? Well, first of all, once our pet is dead, there goes our <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> offense.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Not to mention, the casting time of pets is long, so the chances of getting new defense out without any defense is slim. Compare to root or snare. Once they're gone, they cast quickly. So getting defense in a pinch is npnpnp. <br>
<br>
Root can be used to defend against multiple mobs. Agro too many, just move one away from the crowd and park it. there, it's not doing anyone harm, save a slight hit to your mana pool re-rooting it. Pets on the other hand, are really only defense against 1 thing at a time. Sure, with a DS it could sorta work on 2 or more, but mana wise it would be inferior to just killing 1.<br>
<br>
Root is a low mana cost. Pets take 200 mana for a level 49 pet, 400 for 57-60 GVocs, and 500 mana + 5min refresh + mana gained or lost from swapping equip slots with huge mana values while near full mana. To upkeep a pet, you have to heal it. I don't know the heal heal/mana, but i know it sucks. To prevent pet from taking a lot of damage, you must nuke, which takes even more mana but kills mobs faster. Allowing a pet to defend against more than 1 mob only makes this more inefficient mana-wise. Root, however, for well under half the mana cost of any of our pets, can potentially defend for a longer period of time, against more mobs.<br>
<br>
So, defensively, root is waaaaaaaaay better than a pet. Comparing just to wizard, do you think we're waaaaaaaaaaay better offensively? I don't. We certainly may be better, but it's more of an apples and oranges deal. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 573<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 7:51:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> - Dude, 10 second root is seriously no good. Again, I wouldn't mem it. A spell slot is not worth the mobs being 10 seconds apart. -<br>
